content.description: Fantastic limestoning. Tricky tricky at the fourth bolt or so. Just crank and you'll find it. Beautiful finish on steep jugs.

This climb has some really good, worthy climbing up until the last two bolts. The last 20' becomes very steep and is mostly choss. If one were to add one or two bolts on the false slab just before this section to traverse left into Enemy Line, it would be a fantastic three star line!
content.location: Farthest bolt line to the right.

content.description:
After cruising the first half shared with Flashback (11b/c), head right through an overhanging lip with hidden crimps right in front of your face. A second overhung traverse awaits just before the anchors, but is alll jugs!

It only loses a start because of two chunks of questionable rock. If they were to pass the hammer test, it would be three stars for sure.
content.location: 4th bolt line from the left. Head right.

content.description: Fun crack and face climbing up a dihedral on the left side of the wall.
Fantastic climbing!!! Every move on this route is perfect. Great pockets, edges, overhanging jugs, even some slab thrown in. This route would have a constant line if it was at the Aretes.
content.protection: 8 bolts. 2 bolt anchor with lower off biners.
content.location: Second bolted line from the left

content.description: Mediocre climbing up to a super junky, lame crux bulge around the 4th bolt. It is listed as 5.10b, which is highly inaccurate unless a hold has broken or you stray far left to reach the bolts. Choss above the last bolt as well.
content.protection: 8 bolts, two bolt anchor with lower off biners out right.
content.location: Leftmost bolted route and starts just to the right of a cave (great shade for lunch)
